AN ACT relating to peace officers; creating the [Blue] Purple Ribbon Task Force
on Firefighter and Peace Officer Wellness; setting forth the
membership and duties of the Task Force; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 This bill creates the [Blue] Purple Ribbon Task Force on Firefighter and Peace Officer
2 Wellness to review the existing policies of this State concerning personal wellness initiatives
3 that account for the mental and physical health of firefighters, peace officers and other law
4 enforcement personnel. This bill also: (1) prescribes the membership and duties of the Task
5 Force; and (2) requires the Task Force to submit a written report describing its work and
6 recommendations for transmittal to the Senate and Assembly Standing Committees on
7 Government Affairs for the 84th Session of the Legislature.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. 1. The [Blue] Purple Ribbon Task Force on Firefighter and
2 Peace Officer Wellness is hereby created. The Task Force consists of the following
3 [eight] nine members:
4 (a) Two members appointed by the Majority Leader of the Senate;
5 (b) One member appointed by the Minority Leader of the Senate;
6 (c) [Two] Three members appointed by the Governor;
7 (d) Two members appointed by the Speaker of the Assembly; and
8 (e) One member appointed by the Minority Leader of the Assembly.
9 2. To the extent practicable, membership of the Task Force must include,
10 without limitation:
11 (a) A representative from a local government;

